00:00:03.949 --> 00:00:06.160
How to Clean a Fireplace.

00:00:06.160 --> 00:00:10.420
Cleaning a fireplace can be as much fun as
filing your bicuspids with a wood rasp, but

00:00:10.420 --> 00:00:13.710
homey comforts and family safety come at a
price.

00:00:13.710 --> 00:00:21.360
You will need Safety goggles A paper mask
Old clothes A garbage pail Trash bags Drop

00:00:21.360 --> 00:00:29.890
cloths A whisk broom A shop vacuum A nylon
scrub brush Warm water 1 c. chlorine bleach

00:00:29.890 --> 00:00:38.170
Rubber gloves A large bucket Rags and towels
Newspapers Glass cleaner Knee pads (optional)

00:00:38.170 --> 00:00:39.640
(optional) (optional) and oven cleaner (optional)
(optional) (optional).

00:00:39.640 --> 00:00:40.700
Step 1.

00:00:40.700 --> 00:00:43.930
Put on your protective eyewear, paper mask,
and old clothing.

00:00:43.930 --> 00:00:48.420
With a large pail lined with a garbage bag
by the fireplace, and a drop cloth in place,

00:00:48.420 --> 00:00:50.410
extract large debris from the fireplace.

00:00:50.410 --> 00:00:52.920
Wear knee pads to reduce discomfort.

00:00:52.920 --> 00:00:53.920
Step 2.

00:00:53.920 --> 00:00:57.590
Sweep up ash and soot and scoop into the garbage
bag.

00:00:57.590 --> 00:01:00.560
Vacuum residual soot and ashes out of the
fireplace with a shop vacuum.

00:01:00.560 --> 00:01:05.700
Avoid using a home vacuum to clean the fireplace;
the filter may clog.

00:01:05.700 --> 00:01:06.730
Step 3.

00:01:06.730 --> 00:01:12.240
Drape drop cloths against the interior walls,
and scrape and brush off any remaining flakes.

00:01:12.240 --> 00:01:14.490
Transfer the waste to the trash bag.

00:01:14.490 --> 00:01:15.539
Step 4.

00:01:15.539 --> 00:01:18.929
Mix 1 gallon warm water and bleach in the
bucket.

00:01:18.929 --> 00:01:22.679
Scrub away the last grime, using the brush
tip and collecting everything on the drop

00:01:22.679 --> 00:01:23.679
cloth.

00:01:23.679 --> 00:01:24.770
Step 5.

00:01:24.770 --> 00:01:27.390
Scour the fireplace floor with the cleaning
solution.

00:01:27.390 --> 00:01:29.869
Soak up solution using paper towels.

00:01:29.869 --> 00:01:34.499
Discard in the garbage bag and wipe up any
remaining water with old rags.

00:01:34.499 --> 00:01:35.499
Step 6.

00:01:35.499 --> 00:01:37.460
Take the fireplace grates outside.

00:01:37.460 --> 00:01:42.069
Place grates on layers of newspaper and clean
with oven cleaner or bleach and water.

00:01:42.069 --> 00:01:43.259
Step 7.

00:01:43.259 --> 00:01:46.900
Use glass cleaner and newspapers to clean
glass fireplace doors.

00:01:46.900 --> 00:01:48.729
Polish any exterior metal.

00:01:48.729 --> 00:01:53.609
When finished, clean the entire area with
fresh water and dirt-free towels and let dry.

00:01:53.609 --> 00:01:54.609
Repeat the process at least once a year.

00:01:54.609 --> 00:01:55.609
Did you know Did you know?

00:01:55.609 --> 00:02:00.350
Air inside your home, laden with mold, dander,
radon, and volatile organic compounds, can

00:02:00.350 --> 00:02:03.239
be up to 10 times worse than outdoor air pollution.

